title: Salford man died after taking too many painkillers
text: Father-of-one labourer, 40, died in his sleep 'after accidentally taking too many painkillers for his bad back' Ty Porter, 40, from Salford, died with huge amount of morphine in body Labourer had been suffering from debilitating back pain from the age of 13 18 months before his death he broke his foot jumping from girlfriend's window His family insists that he was careful with morphine and would never kill himself Greater Manchester Senior Coroner Jennifer Leeming said it was tragic accident
